'''Irreligion in Mozambique''' is not uncommon among Mozambicans largely in part due to past government suppression of religion. Though [[Christianity]] predominates,<ref>{{cite news|title= Maputo Journal: In Marx's Garden: Atheism Wilts, Faith Blooms|publisher= [[The New York Times]]|date=|url= https://www.nytimes.com/1988/05/10/world/maputo-journal-in-marx-s-garden-atheism-wilts-faith-blooms.html|accessdate=2014-04-06}}</ref> according to census results 19% of the country do not identify with a religion.
